{
  "local_port": 53176,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I register my mobile number with UAN?",
  "response": "To register your mobile number with your Universal Account Number (UAN) for the Employee Provident Fund Organization (EPFO) in India, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the EPFO Member Portal**: Go to the EPFO member portal at [epfindia.gov.in](http://epfindia.gov.in).\n\n2. **Select 'For Employees'**: Click on the 'For Employees' tab.\n\n3. **UAN Member Portal**: Navigate to the UAN Member Portal link or directly visit [uanmembers.epfoservices.in](http://uanmembers.epfoservices.in).\n\n4. **Login to Your Account**: If you already have your UAN, you can log in using your UAN and password. If you do not have an account, you will need to generate your UAN first using the \"Activate UAN\" option.\n\n5. **Profile Section**: Once you are logged in, go to the 'Manage' section and select 'Modify Basic Details' or click on 'Profile'.\n\n6. **Update Mobile Number**: Here, you can enter your mobile number or update it if it has changed.\n\n7. **OTP Verification**: An OTP (One-Time Password) will be sent to the mobile number you provided. Enter this OTP to verify your mobile number.\n\n8. **Confirmation**: After successfully entering the OTP, your mobile number will be updated in the UAN database.\n\n9. **Log Out**: Once you have updated your details, make sure to log out of your account.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- Ensure that the mobile number you are trying to register is active, as the OTP will be sent to this number.\n- If you are unable to do this online, you can also visit your employer or the nearest EPFO office for assistance.\n\nBy following these steps, your mobile number will be successfully registered with your UAN.",
